			<div id="post-112" class="hentry p1 post publish author-katt category-drawing tag-doodle tag-skerple y2010 m09 d03 h05">
    			<h1 class="entry-title">Skerple Friday: Skerpy Puff</h1>
<div class="entry-meta"><span class="author vcard">By <a class="url fn n" href="/author/admin/" title="View all posts by Katt">Katt</a></span><span class="meta-sep"> | </span><span class="entry-date"><abbr class="published" title="2010-09-03T09:00:55-0400">September 3, 2010</abbr></span></div><!-- .entry-meta -->
				<div class="entry-content">
<p>I was sick last week, and I&#8217;ve been having some trouble getting quality sleep this week, and I know I know NO EXCUSES, but it&#8217;s been a little tough to find the energy to draw or blog. I&#8217;m going on vacation this weekend, though! I&#8217;ll be able to practice drawing people in the airport. And the person sitting next to me on the plane will be like &#8220;ooh, you&#8217;re an artist? whatcha drawing?&#8221; and I&#8217;ll be all WHAT&#8217;S IT TO YA because I&#8217;m an introvert and pretty bad at socializing. I would like to preemptively apologize to the person sitting next to me on the plane.</p>
<p><a href="/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/skerple-puff.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-113" title="skerple-puff" src="/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/skerple-puff.png" alt="" width="438" height="688" /></a>When I first moved to this town, I kept seeing a probably-feral cat sleeping in the lot next door. I tried to be his friend, but feral cats are about as friendly toward humans as I am to my hypothetical airplane seatmate.</p>
<p>He was all white and longhaired, which seems like the worst possible fur choice for a cat who lives on the street, except in winter. He had that kinda ugly feral cat face &#8211; you know what I&#8217;m talking about? Sort of a longer face with squinty eyes, less open and kittenish, more like a perpetually-irritated lion. And boy was he dirty. I started calling him Dirrty Puff.</p>
<p>Our cat, Bonus Cat, used to be a friend of his. One day I was looking out the window at Dirrty&#8217;s usual spot, and there was a bonus cat hanging out with him, hence the name.</p>
<p>The months went on. Bonus became our friend, but Dirrty decided to relocate operations so he wouldn&#8217;t be bothered by me. I stopped seeing him regularly, and then I stopped seeing him altogether. I saw him once that summer, and then I saw him in January, and that was it. I feared he&#8217;d died at some point during the winter, because he didn&#8217;t seem like a healthy cat to begin with (Bonus was cleaner and had much more energy, but it still took four weeks of medication to get him well enough to be neutered). I was sad about that, but you can&#8217;t help someone who doesn&#8217;t want to be helped.</p>
<p>Anyway, I was walking home two days ago, and I SAW DIRRTY PUFF. He was walking up a porch, looked at me, and ran off across the street in true Puff fashion. Same face and everything, but he looked a lot cleaner. Maybe he has somewhere to stay?</p>
<p>I tried to capture his face here, but it&#8217;s not right at all. Cats are hard enough to draw, more so from memory.</p>

									</div>
